  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6982.55 sitting just below the massive 7000 gamma wall (15.7B), dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push above this level as they hedge their long gamma exposure. The PIN regime confirms dealers will fade momentum - they're likely buying the recent dip from above 7000 and will continue selling rallies back toward this key strike. Watch 7000 as the primary resistance where dealer selling intensifies, while 6893 (GEX flip) and 6800 (max negative gamma) provide downside support levels where dealer buying kicks in.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect strong resistance at 7000 with sideways to slightly lower action in the near term.",
